Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 215.

In the 24 hours since the last WHO update:

- The Americas region reported 60.9% of the global newly reported cases and 78.6% of newly reported deaths for this 24-hour period, maintaining its dominance as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 7.9 million cases. The USA reported 40.2% (69 641) of cases, Brazil 39.2% (67 860), Colombia 4.3% (7390), Mexico 3.5% (6019), Argentina 3.3% (5782), Peru 2.6% (4463), and Chile 1.4% (2357).

- The European region reported 7.9% of the global newly reported cases and 4.6% of the newly confirmed deaths globally. Russia reported 25.8% (5811) of the regional newly confirmed cases, followed by Spain 11.6% (2615), Kazakhstan 7.5% (1687), Romania 4.9% (1112), Ukraine 4.3% (972), Kyrgyzstan 4.1% (921), Turkey 4.1% (913), and France 4.1% (945). Spain's 14-day population-based incidence rate has gone from a low of 7.74 per 100 000 population on 25 Jun 2020 to 37.94 today (24 Jul 2020), continuing to increase on a daily basis (calculated from the daily spreadsheet we maintain with data from https://www.mscbs.gob.es/profesionales/saludPublica/ccayes/alertasActual/nCov-China/documentos/Actualizacion_169_COVID-19.pdf) and Italy has increased its 7-day average by 22.2% over the preceding 7-day period, a sign there are increases in transmission of the SARS-CoV-2 (calculated from the daily spreadsheet we maintain with data from http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto).

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.7% of the global newly reported cases and 4.9% of global newly reported fatalities. Iran reported 19.8% (2621) of the regional newly reported cases, followed by Iraq 17.8% (2361), Saudi Arabia 16.9% (2238), Pakistan 9.1% (1209), Oman 8.3% (1009), Kuwait 5.2% (687), Egypt 5.0% (668), Palestinian Authority 4.5% (596), Qatar 2.8% (373), and Bahrain 2.7% (359). Pakistan is decreasing its daily case count steadily during the month of July 2020, while at the same time cases are increasing in Iraq and Oman. This region remains highly active, with multiple countries still in a surge mode.

- The African region reported 6.0% of the global newly reported cases and 2.2% of newly reported fatalities. South Africa reported 77.3% (13 104) of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by Kenya 4.7% (796), Algeria 3.6% (612), Nigeria 3.6% (604), and Ethiopia 2.4% (409). Since the beginning of July 2020, South Africa has reported daily new case counts of greater than 10 000 15 of the 24 days.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.4% of the global newly reported cases and 0.38% of global deaths. The Philippines reported 52.8% (2121) of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Japan 23.1% (927), Australia 10.2% (410), Singapore 8.8% (354), China 3.5% (139), and South Korea 1.0% (41). Japan has been steadily increasing daily case counts over the past week.

- The South East Asia region reported 19.1% of the global newly reported cases and 9.3% of global deaths. India reported 90.9% (49 310) of newly reported cases in the region, followed by Bangladesh 5.3% (2856) and Indonesia 3.5% (1906). India continues to be the driving force of the dominance of this region.

Impression: The overall picture is basically the same. The ordering of the regions has the Americas having the highest disease load and newly confirmed cases on a daily basis followed by the South East Asia region, then Europe followed by the Eastern Mediterranean, followed by the Africa region and the Western Pacific representing the lowest daily caseload of all the regions.

Figure 2. The epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by date of report and WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 24 Jul 2020, at the source URL above is an excellent visual representation of the epidemic as described in the above text. - Mod.MPP]

